source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1960, 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010, 2020 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2022; (f) International estimates used up to 2021; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the (a) 1950 Census; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) 2005, 2015 ACS survey estimates have been considered.  Note: HMD populations 1950--1958 (incl.) do not include Hawaii and Alaska. Official US Census Bureau estimates are available for the usual resident population that do include these states.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2023; (b) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2022; (c) adjusted for underregistration; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1960 Census; (e) International estimates used up to 2020. In addition, the (a) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010, 2020 censuses and 1990-2010 Education Stats and 2005, 2015 ACS; (b) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980, 1990 censuses and 1952, 1954, 1957, 1959 Survey and 1994 CPS have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2017; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2022; (c) International estimates used up to 2021.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2017; (b) registered infant and child deaths through 2022.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) official figures of net international migration flows, and assumed subsequent trends in international migration; (b) estimates of migrant flows, and assumed subsequent trends in international migration; (c) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (d) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (e) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
